[
    {
        "content": "<p>For a topos <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{T}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">T</span></span></span></span></span>, the subobject functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo>:</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mo>−</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Ω</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo>:</mo><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow></msup><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathscr{P}:= [-,\\Omega]: \\mathrm{T^{op}\\to Pos}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.36687em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Ω</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.664392em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathrm mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">P</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">s</span></span></span></span></span> is lax cartesian, and this implies that it is lax closed: there's a canonical map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>A</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathscr{P}([A,B])\\to [\\mathscr{P}(A),\\mathscr{P}(B)]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> given by currying of evaluation.</p>\n<p>In the case of sets or presheaves, we can also go back: given a map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>:</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F:\\mathscr{P}(A)\\to \\mathscr{P}(B)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, we can form the subobject <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>U</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mtext>  </mtext><msub><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊆</mo><mi>F</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mo>↣</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>A</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{f:A\\to B\\; |\\; \\forall U\\in \\mathscr{P}(A).\\; f_!(U)\\subseteq F(U)\\} \\rightarrowtail [A,B]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.33610799999999996em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊆</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel amsrm\">↣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> -- all maps which \"respect\" <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span>. This gives that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathscr{P}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathscr\" style=\"margin-right:0.08078em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span> is also \"colax closed\".</p>\n<p>How can this \"colaxor\" be constructed in a general topos? I think it will always look basically like the one above.</p>",
        "id": 198479794,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590173233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe you can use the Mitchell-Benabou language to write down that subobject in any topos, more or less like how you just did in Set.</p>",
        "id": 198480491,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173556
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks, that's just what I was about to say. That \"set\" formula might actually be right in general.</p>",
        "id": 198480600,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590173619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For some reason I haven't yet gotten comfortable enough with Mitchell-Benabou to think \"oh, I can just write it like this and it works\".</p>",
        "id": 198480717,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590173683
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can probably say </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> f_! (U) = \\{b \\in B | \\exists a \\in A . f(a) = b \\} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.33610799999999996em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">b</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">a</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"mord\">.</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">a</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">b</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 198480758,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173707
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You never <em>need</em> to use the Mitchell-Benabou language to describe things; the whole point is that it just  captures all the stuff you can already do in a topos.   But sometimes it can be more convenient.</p>",
        "id": 198480853,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At the very least this would be a good excuse to learn more about the Mitchell-Benabou language and what you can and cannot say in it.</p>",
        "id": 198480972,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Wait, why do I want to re-express <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f_!(U)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.33610799999999996em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>? Can't we just reference that adjoint directly?</p>",
        "id": 198480992,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590173831
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Since you have a very specific thing you're trying to express, you'll be highly motivated to learn the precise limitations of the Mitchell-Benabou language!</p>",
        "id": 198481046,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173859
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So yeah, you're suggesting that we can probably use that formula above as a guide for how to actually construct the map in a general topos.</p>",
        "id": 198481049,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590173861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, you can reference that adjoint directly, but if you're trying to work with it <em>in</em> the Mitchell-Benabou language, it's good to know how to express it in that language.    It's like if you're talking about a dog in Spanish, it's good to know the Spanish word for \"dog\".</p>",
        "id": 198481196,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173921
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm all for Spanglish but...</p>",
        "id": 198481227,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590173949
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There are probably people here (maybe not right this second) who understand this stuff a lot better than me.  But I found that <em>Sheaves in Geometry and Logic</em> and McLarty's <em>Elementary Categories, Elementary Toposes</em> have pretty user-friendly intros to the Mitchell-Benabou language.  My own study of it was limited by not having anything I wanted to do with it!</p>",
        "id": 198481515,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174082
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I just thought that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f_! = \\exists_f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.33610799999999996em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.980548em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> was a part of the language.</p>",
        "id": 198481622,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590174124
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's hard to find a canonical presentation of the language as a type theory. A somewhat relaxed explanation like in the Sheaves book doesn't make me feel secure in exactly what the language is.</p>",
        "id": 198481629,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590174127
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh-oh, you're turning into a logician!  Nervous if you're not surrounded by a protective layer of symbols.</p>",
        "id": 198481681,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the one in Borceux is a bit more thorough, but still not exactly what I might consider formal.</p>",
        "id": 198481683,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590174163
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, I guess you want exactly what I don't.  So take my recommendations and <em>don't read those</em>.</p>",
        "id": 198481728,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174188
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you haven't heard, we are now required to wear a protective layer of symbols when we go out.</p>",
        "id": 198481759,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590174204
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I should design some sort of face mask with mathematical symbols on it.</p>",
        "id": 198481864,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174259
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anyway, yeah, some sort of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists_f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.980548em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> thing should be in the M-B language, though I'm still more comfortable with good old quantification over variables <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists x \\in X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.73354em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 198481965,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174318
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, I see Mac Lane and Moerdijk use just old-fashioned things like <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists x \\in X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.73354em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> in their version of the M-B language.</p>",
        "id": 198482090,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But it doesn't really matter ultimately, I bet.</p>",
        "id": 198482104,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174394
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It must be just a choice of conventions.</p>",
        "id": 198482135,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1590174409
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, so they have an example of using <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi>Y</mi><mi>X</mi></msup><mtext>  </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∀</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>Y</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>X</mi><mtext>  </mtext><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Epi}(X,Y) = \\{f\\in Y^X\\; |\\; \\forall y\\in Y\\; \\exists x\\in X\\; f(x)=y\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">E</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">p</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">i</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0913309999999998em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413309999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∀</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.73354em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span> to derive the \"subobject of epimorphisms\". I'll study that, and try to do the same for the \"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> respects <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span></span></span></span>\" formula above.</p>",
        "id": 198482350,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Williams",
        "timestamp": 1590174531
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275920\">John Baez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/230087-theory.3A-topos.20theory/topic/subobject.20functor.20colax.20closed/near/198481965\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Anyway, yeah, some sort of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists_f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.980548em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> thing should be in the M-B language, though I'm still more comfortable with good old quantification over variables <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∃</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\exists x \\in X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.73354em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∃</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">∈</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In MLTT, you quantify over variables with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Sigma_{x : A}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">Σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">x</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">:</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">A</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, even though in the category theory the dependent sum is interpreted as <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Σ</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Sigma_f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.969438em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">Σ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, so I'd imagine it's the same with the MB language. The language isn't meant to look exactly like the categorical structure, or you could just as well not use the language.</p>",
        "id": 198482384,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1590174556
    },
    {
